      <p>
        If lifecycle email is new territory, read in this order: (1) this hub for vertical routing, (2) your store-type guide top to bottom, (3) <a class="link" href="/use-cases/welcome-series">welcome series</a> and <a class="link" href="/use-cases/post-purchase">post-purchase</a> use cases, (4) finalist comparison at <a class="link" href="/compare">/compare</a>, (5) full tool profile for your chosen platform at <a class="link" href="/apps">/apps</a>. Do not read all twelve vertical guides — read yours deeply and skim adjacent verticals only when catalog behavior overlaps (beauty plus subscription boxes, for example).
      </p>
      <p>
        Retention leads at five hundred or more orders per month should block eight weeks for implementation per the rollout plans in each guide. Founders building nights-and-weekends should pick Sequenzy or Omnisend for speed, one vertical guide, and a maximum of two concurrent flow builds. Agency partners scoping client stacks should use the selection matrix above as a shortcut — then confirm with client order volume, subscription penetration, and team capacity before recommending Klaviyo or ActiveCampaign overhead.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every store-type guide names five primary tools plus Shopify Email as native baseline where relevant. Comparison tables list seventeen apps so you see the full wall without opening every <a class="link" href="/apps">tool profile</a>. Tool review sections go four paragraphs deep per pick — enough to understand fit without leaving the guide, though we link there for pricing detail and feature lists.
      </p>
      <p>
        The twelve verticals cover the majority of Shopify Plus and growth-stage merchant searches we encounter in retention consulting: apparel and fashion, beauty and supplements (replenishment-heavy), jewelry and high-AOV (consideration-heavy), home goods (project-heavy), food beverage and pet (consumption-heavy), digital and POD (velocity-heavy), subscription boxes (retention-state-heavy), and B2B wholesale (account-heavy). If you run multiple models — beauty subscription box plus DTC — merge priorities from both guides and resolve conflicts in favor of subscription state suppression over promotional sends.
      </p>
      <p>
